Passing a mongodb cursor by value to a function, then re-using the cursor in multiple iterations causes Apache to crash without an error log entry.

e.g. The following crashes Apache
function print_matrix($mongo_cursor){
	$i = 0;
	for($i=0;$i<200;$i++)
	{
		foreach ($mongo_cursor as $obj) {
			var_dump($obj);		
		}
	}
}

Passing by reference fixes the problem:

function print_matrix(&$mongo_cursor){
	$i = 0;
	for($i=0;$i<200;$i++)
	{
		foreach ($mongo_cursor as $obj) {
			var_dump($obj);		
		}
	}
}

I note that passing by value may not be the correct way to use a mongodb cursor. However I would have expected at the very least an Apache error log entry to say why it crashed.

